      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SMOKE SCREEN (8) ran a most encouraging race first up at Ballarat over this trip, only nosed out on that occasion, putting up a strong rating in the process. If she can land close enough from the inside gate she'll go close. INVINCIBLE LOVER (7) has shown plenty of ability in three runs to date, second last time out (albeit beaten 8 lengths) by a speedy one at Cranbourne. If she's got another run in the tank she can break through. STERNIN (9) has been thereabouts in three runs this time in, close up behind SMOKE SCREEN at Ballarat last time. She'll be up on speed and in this for a long way. EXIT STRATEGY (5) is a filly by Bivouac on debut for the Douglas yard who has to be respected with Williams booked.",
